task.summary: Default task
Implemented parts of the StructureBuilder
The Structure Menu is now working, except for the visualization.
The structure can now be loaded from python and the bounding box will be shown.
The structure now gets shown in the structure creator. Bugs remain.
The structure size and amount of frames now gets send from Python to Unity when sending the structure.
The cellbox now gets drawn correctly for orthorhombic structures.
The cell borders are now spheres. This way,the vertices look better. The midpoint of the structure should now be calculated correctly.
When choosing a job in the explorer, the structure will be shown (not yet as an animation). The scale of the structure in Structure mode and Explorer mode can now be changed.
The cellbox now has a collider that exactly contains the cellbox, even if the cellbox is not cubic.
Fixed a bug that the cellbox would be shown wrong after moving the structure. The Job panel now loads more data from pyiron. Code cleanup.
When loading a job and switching into calculate menu, it will automatically set the mode to md, minimize or static, depending on the mode that has been loaded.
The md panel now loads its data from pyiron on start up. The temperature is not yet working.
The calculate menu now loads all necessary data on mode startup from pyiron
Reworked the thermometer and temperature slider (they are now working again).
The progressbar now works with the new structure system.
Removed some old code. Added mocks for the new implementation.
Refactored and cleaned up some code.
Moved some external plugins again to the plugins folder (to shorten compile times), but this time it is still possible to build.
The element of the structure can now be determined by using the periodic table.
In the structure menu, the button used for choosing the element now has the color of the current element.
Added a new build for the Oculus Quest
The fixed some bugs with the element button.
Implemented a text that shows up when the program is loading.
Fixed a bug that the potentials dropdown would show the wrong potentials, because it did not update and just showed all potentials until it set the current potential.
When some structures can't run because of a yet unknown error, there will now be an error message
Fixed a bug that the program would crash when trying to load an element that is not in the LocalElementData File
Fixed a bug that the program would freeze if the server suddenly stops responding (e.g. because it crashed)
Fixed a bug that the program would load endlessly when trying to load somethin asynchronous. Receiving a large file from python now seems to be asynchronous.
The Program can now automatically reconnect after loosing connection to the server.
The structure now looks deactivated while the program has no connection to the server
The structure now looks deactivated while the program asynchronously sends a message
